1
00:01:45,370 --> 00:01:47,990
中国提供40%的救市金  
China provides 40% of the bailout,

2
00:01:47,990 --> 00:01:51,150
国际货币基金组织提供另外40%
the IMF provides another 40%

3
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:55,280
一个美中能源企业的联盟
and a consortium of American and Chinese energy companies

4
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,960
解决剩下的20%
tackles the remaining 20%,

5
00:01:56,960 --> 00:02:00,170
我们以开采权作为交换
in exchange for which they get drilling rights.

6
00:02:00,410 --> 00:02:04,190
美方只用拿出八千亿中的一千五百亿
The US would only have to contribute 150 of the $800 billion.

7
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:06,000
俄国企业会监督生产
Russian companies would oversee production

8
00:02:06,010 --> 00:02:07,730
获取一小部分收益
and get a slice of the revenues.

9
00:02:07,730 --> 00:02:09,980
这些是拟开发区
These are the proposed development zones.

10
00:02:10,010 --> 00:02:11,930
我们割让了开采权吗
We split the drilling rights?

11
00:02:11,930 --> 00:02:13,860
是的  先生  中国出了更多钱
Yes, sir. China puts in more money,

12
00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:16,660
我们就拿出我们的开采技术
but we contribute our drilling technology.

13
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:18,930
分享技术真的好吗
Should we really be sharing that?

14
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,840
他们早就想从我们这儿偷学了
They're already trying to hack it from us.

15
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:22,380
佩特罗夫同意了吗
Has Petrov agreed to this?

16
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:23,440
我打算在
I'm planning to propose

17
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:25,930
德国勃兰登堡的七国峰会上跟他提
it to him in Brandenburg at the G7 Summit.

18
00:02:25,930 --> 00:02:28,210
我们已邀请俄国和中国参加
We've invited Russia and China to attend,

19
00:02:28,210 --> 00:02:29,580
但国会批准前
but we didn't wanna move forward

20
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:31,700
我们不想采取进一步行动
until we had congressional approval.

21
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:35,880
-鲍勃  -我们该私下谈
- Bob? - We should discuss privately.

22
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:38,010
你要亲自去勃兰登堡吗
You're going to Brandenburg yourself?

23
00:02:38,490 --> 00:02:41,410
如果他的病情继续恶化
If his health continues to worsen--

24
00:02:41,410 --> 00:02:43,060
之后再看情况
We'll assess as we get closer,

25
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:44,990
但如果情况悲观我就不去
but, no, I'll stay here if it looks dire.

26
00:02:44,990 --> 00:02:47,480
我们应该起草拨款申请
We should probably draft an appropriation

27
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:50,050
以防需要举办国葬
in case we need to pay for a state funeral.

28
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:28,320
-道格  -部长女士
- Doug. - Madam Secretary.

29
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:33,530
我可以去白宫的
I could've come to the White House.

30
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:33,770
{\an8}梅瑞迪斯·李
卫生和人类服务部部长

31
00:03:35,930 --> 00:03:38,740
器官供应组织要听命于你
The organ network, it answers to you.

32
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:41,760
说对了一半  从监管方面来说...
Yes and no. Uh, in a regulatory capacity--

33
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:44,700
你有权力调整器官接受人名单
You have the power to modify the recipient list.

34
00:03:44,730 --> 00:03:46,470
顺序由供应组织决定
That's up to the network.

35
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:48,030
他们有专家委员会...
They have an expert committee that--

36
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:51,150
总统的生命不能由一个委员会决定
The president's life isn't going to be decided by a committee.

37
00:03:51,650 --> 00:03:53,460
我给你看点东西
Let me show you something.

38
00:04:00,190 --> 00:04:04,250
他昨天是第三位  第一位已经移植了
He was number three yesterday. Number one got a transplant.

39
00:04:00,410 --> 00:04:03,920
{\an8}安东尼·莫雷蒂
弗兰西斯·安德伍德

40
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:08,190
总统现在是第二位  他活的机会很大
Makes the president number two. His chances are very good.

41
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:12,670
但这个安东尼·莫雷蒂再过几小时就要死了
But this man, Anthony Moretti, he's just hours away from dying.

42
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,380
{\an8}安东尼·莫雷蒂
弗兰西斯·安德伍德

43
00:04:12,670 --> 00:04:13,840
那就让他死
Then let him die.

44
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:19,310
我不会这么做的
I'm not doing this.

45
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,780
不仅违法  也有违道德
It's not just the law. It's the ethics--

46
00:04:21,780 --> 00:04:23,720
那就改变你的道德标准
Then change your ethics.

47
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:26,490
不然你就辞职  让副部长打这个电话
Or you can resign, and your deputy can make this call.

48
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:29,040
如果他不愿意  他也辞职
And if he won't, then he can resign, too.

49
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:32,230
我会把这整个部门翻个底朝天  找到我需要的人
I will strip away this entire department until I find who I need.

50
00:04:38,380 --> 00:04:39,580
打电话吧
Now make the call.

51
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,840
{\an8}波利跳

52
00:04:43,590 --> 00:04:45,200
-好  我上去了  -你用过吗
- Okay, I'm on. - You ever use it?

53
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,390
不  我一般用谷歌
No, I use Google.

54
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,630
它市场份额很小
Uh, it's a small market share,

55
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:49,750
但一个月仍有数十亿次搜索
but still, it's billions of searches a month.

56
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:53,350
如果一个候选人有更多点击量
Now, what if a certain candidate got more hits,

57
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,570
排名更靠前
was ranked higher,

58
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:57,030
正面报道多过负面报道呢
more positive coverage favored over negative coverage?

59
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,950
如果那个候选人是威廉·康威呢
What if that candidate was William Conway?

60
00:05:01,930 --> 00:05:04,350
操纵搜索结果  公众会与他们反目的
Manipulating searches? The public would turn on them.

61
00:05:04,350 --> 00:05:05,960
帮他们拉到了上千万的选票
It gets them millions of votes. 

62
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,150
能弄到确凿证据吗
Can you get me solid proof?

63
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:09,350
我不会参与这样的事
Well, I am not getting involved in something like this.

64
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:12,550
我只会作为朋友  给你友善的建议
What I will give you is advice as a friend.

65
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,070
别把一年的时光浪费在安德伍德夫妇身上
Don't waste a year of your life on the Underwoods.

66
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:16,810
他们已经输掉了竞选
They've already lost the election

67
00:05:16,810 --> 00:05:18,570
而且自己还没有意识到
and they don't even realize it.

68
00:05:19,890 --> 00:05:21,770
我知道你只想帮忙
I know you're only trying to help,

69
00:05:21,770 --> 00:05:23,860
也明白你很担心
and I'm sure you must feel frightened

70
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:24,630
弗兰克的情况
about Frank's condition--

71
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:26,670
你没必要拐弯抹角  凯茜
You don't have to be delicate, Cathy.

72
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,750
我希望你不要干涉我的工作
I'd like you to let me do my job.

73
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:32,210
中国不能成为谈判的核心
China cannot be at the center of this negotiation, 

74
00:05:32,210 --> 00:05:33,150
雷蒙德·塔斯克也不行
or Raymond Tusk.

75
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:34,490
把石油公司牵扯进来
Involving the oil companies 

76
00:05:34,490 --> 00:05:38,040
是我们赢得共和党支持的唯一办法
is the only shot we have at winning Republican support.

77
00:05:39,170 --> 00:05:42,920
还记得那次玩啤酒乒乓球  你放水让我赢吗
Do you remember when we played beer pong and you let me win?

78
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:45,190
我们两个就坐在那边
The two of us were sitting right over there,

79
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:46,190
那两张椅子上
in those two chairs,

80
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:48,670
你征求了我的意见
and you asked me for my advice.

81
00:05:48,670 --> 00:05:49,680
那是一条好建议
It was good advice.

82
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,440
你也接受了  我不明白你现在为什么不肯接受
And you listened to it. I don't know why you won't now.

83
00:05:52,450 --> 00:05:55,770
你上次提的是建设性意见  这次却不是
You were proposing a way forward. This time you're not.

84
00:05:55,770 --> 00:05:59,050
与你不同  我是由参议院委任的
Well, unlike you, my nomination was confirmed by the Senate,

85
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:01,470
因为他们相信我知道自己在做什么
because they believed I knew what I was doing.

86
00:06:01,490 --> 00:06:03,270
很抱歉  克莱尔  但在我看来
Forgive me, Claire, but it seems to me

87
00:06:03,270 --> 00:06:05,730
你正在利用现在的局面
that you are taking advantage of the situation

88
00:06:05,730 --> 00:06:07,220
行使一些你无权行使的权力
to assert authority you don't have a right to assert.

89
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:09,880
凯茜  弗兰西斯现在不在
Cathy, you don't have Francis right now.

90
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:11,000
我是你的最佳选择
I'm the best thing you've got,

91
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,460
请与我共同解决这个问题吧
so please work with me on this.

92
00:06:12,470 --> 00:06:14,960
国会不会批准的
Congress will never approve this.

93
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:16,870
你在浪费大家的时间
You're just wasting everybody's time.

94
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:18,800
共和党会支持的
The Republicans will get in line.

95
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,100
不是共和党  是民主党
Not the Republicans, the Democrats.

96
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:22,670
我跟杰姬·夏普谈过
I spoke to Jackie Sharp.

97
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:24,960
当她得知是你制定了这个计划...
When she heard you developed this plan...

98
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:30,780
她是个厉害的女人  克莱尔  而且很有说服力
She's a formidable woman, Claire, and very persuasive.

99
00:06:42,850 --> 00:06:46,630
-雷米·丹顿  -雷米  我们得谈谈杰姬
- Remy Danton. - Remy, we need to talk about Jackie.

100
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,300
多美的夜晚
Such a nice night.

101
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,220
我们出去走走吧
Let's go somewhere outside.

102
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:06,580
你想去哪
And where do you wanna go?

103
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:08,690
带我去海湾吧
Take me to the bay.

104
00:07:09,260 --> 00:07:10,760
我们去裸泳
We'll go skinny-dipping.

105
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:13,050
你不是只有几个小时时间吗
I thought you only had a couple hours.

106
00:07:13,050 --> 00:07:14,980
我可以找到借口的
I'll make up some excuse.

107
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,380
我在酒店待腻了
I'm sick of hotel rooms.

108
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:21,410
咱俩明天还有事呢
We both got a big day tomorrow.

109
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:23,660
你怎么这么扫兴
Why are you being no fun?

110
00:07:23,660 --> 00:07:25,840
因为你要搅黄我的法案
Because you're trying to kill my bill.

111
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:28,830
你不是想见我  你是来游说我的
You didn't wanna see me. You wanted to lobby me.

112
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:31,140
-杰姬  -是谁告诉你我反对的
- Jackie, listen - Who told you I was against it?

113
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:35,900
博奇的幕僚长
Birch's Chief of Staff.

114
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:38,480
我相信你能从中捞到不少钱  但是...
Well, I'm sure you stand to make a lot of money on this, but--

115
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,470
不是因为钱
It's not about the money.

116
00:07:39,470 --> 00:07:41,660
克莱尔不是靠钱说服你的吗
Isn't that how Claire convinced you?

117
00:07:45,130 --> 00:07:46,100
我今晚不想谈
I just wanted to leave it tonight.

118
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:47,420
我不想冲你发火
I didn't wanna be mad at you.

119
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:48,760
我只想
I just wanted...

120
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:57,070
我不明白你为什么要帮她
I don't understand why you're helping her.

121
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,730
你得让博奇同意
You've gotta get Birch on board.

122
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:03,600
安德伍德夫妇欺骗过我
The Underwoods have lied to me,

123
00:08:03,610 --> 00:08:05,510
利用过我  还试图威胁我
they've used me, they've tried to intimidate me.

124
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:06,850
我不知道克莱尔想干什么
I don't know what Claire's up to,

125
00:08:06,850 --> 00:08:08,640
但我绝不会坐以待毙
but I'm not gonna let it happen without a fight,

126
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:10,290
而且国务院都已经反对了
not with the State Department against it.

127
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:11,630
克莱尔知道了
Claire knows.

128
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:15,060
我们俩的事
About you and me.

129
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,480
她有我们的照片
She got photographs 

130
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:22,060
多次同时离开同一家酒店
of us leaving the same hotel at the same time, multiple occasions.

131
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:27,030
送我回我车上
Take me back to my car.

132
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:31,440
-杰姬  听我说  -请掉头
- Jackie, listen... - Turn around now, please.

133
00:08:31,450 --> 00:08:33,320
所以我最近没怎么联系你
It's the reason I haven't been in touch.

134
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,410
我想保护你...
I wanted to protect you... 

135
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:37,610
-但是她提出了  -我不想谈这个
- but she's making-- - I don't wanna talk about it.

136
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:41,120
停车  让我下去  或者送我回去
Just stop the car and let me out or drive me back.

137
00:08:42,890 --> 00:08:43,980
我送你回去
I'll take you back.

138
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,160
再一两天
A day or two.

139
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,910
我们没办法提前通知  总统先生
We might not have much warning, Mr. President.

140
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,460
肝脏如此接近衰竭
When the liver is this close to failure,

141
00:08:54,460 --> 00:08:55,940
一切都有可能突然发生
things can happen suddenly.

142
00:08:55,940 --> 00:08:57,390
你们应该做好准备
You should be prepared.

143
00:08:57,560 --> 00:09:01,030
-他的手是怎么回事  -那是扑翼样震颤
- What's happening with his hands? - It's called asterixis.

144
00:09:01,030 --> 00:09:03,490
当身体无法排除氨时就会发生这种情况
It happens when the body can't clear ammonia.

145
00:09:04,330 --> 00:09:05,870
谢谢你  撒克逊医生
Thank you, Dr. Saxon.

146
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,920
我不去勃兰登堡了
I'm not going to Brandenburg.

147
00:10:21,970 --> 00:10:23,410
不  你必须去
No, you have to.

148
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:27,020
-凯茜会代表我谈判  -在这事上我不信任她
- Cathy will negotiate on my behalf. - I don't trust her on this.

149
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:28,620
我们必须冒这个风险
That's a risk we'll have to take.

150
00:10:28,940 --> 00:10:32,620
我不能冒的风险是当总统去世时我在海外
The risk I won't take is being overseas if the president dies.

151
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,160
我们都不知道国会
We don't even know if Congress

152
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:36,120
会不会批准这次救市拨款
will approve the appropriation for the bailout.

153
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,400
他们会批准的  我会确保他们批准
They will approve it. I'll make sure they do.

154
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:42,120
你现在不该担心这个  克莱尔
You shouldn't be worrying about this now, Claire.

155
00:10:42,670 --> 00:10:44,290
你应该全心关注弗兰克
You should be focused on Frank.

156
00:12:25,170 --> 00:12:26,610
我们得给他上呼吸机
We need to put him on the ventilator 

157
00:12:26,610 --> 00:12:27,680
保护他的呼吸道
to protect his airways.

158
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:30,200
您该走了  夫人  去休息一下
You should go, ma'am. Go get some rest.

159
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:29,210
-现在不是时候  莉安  -非常紧急
- Now's not a good time, LeAnn. - This can't wait.

160
00:13:29,380 --> 00:13:31,270
-怎么了  -波利跳
- What is it? - Pollyhop.

161
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:34,700
-搜索引擎吗  -康威在跟他们合作
- The search engine? - Conway is working with them.

162
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:37,150
他们可以操纵人们搜索的东西
They can manipulate what people search for.

163
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:38,430
给了他们巨大优势
It gives them a huge advantage--

164
00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:39,760
等等  慢点  这是什么意思
Wait, slow down. What does this mean?

165
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:41,590
意思是我们输了
It means that we lose.

166
00:13:42,270 --> 00:13:43,740
康威的名字  他的照片
Conway's name, his image,

167
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:46,550
他们可以控制人们看到什么  强迫人们看
they can control what people see. They can force-feed it.

168
00:13:46,550 --> 00:13:47,640
即便他们不那么做
Even if they're not doing that,

169
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:50,570
即便他们只是在追踪用户  也足以打败我们了
even if they're just tracking users, it's enough to beat us.

170
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:54,060
你知道人们在搜索什么  就知道一切
You know what people are searching for, you know everything,

171
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,170
他们的希望  恐惧
their hopes, their fears, 

172
00:13:55,170 --> 00:13:57,280
他们半夜盯着天花板时
what they're thinking about when they're staring at the ceiling 

173
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:58,380
脑袋里在想什么
in the middle of the night.

174
00:13:58,380 --> 00:14:01,460
-谁告诉你的  -我信任的人
- Who told you this? - Someone I trust.

175
00:14:03,420 --> 00:14:04,770
我现在不能处理这件事
I can't deal with this right now.

176
00:14:04,770 --> 00:14:06,280
我们得想点办法  克莱尔  否则大选
We have to do something, Claire, or the election--

177
00:14:06,290 --> 00:14:07,920
莉安  我丈夫刚刚痉挛发作
LeAnn, my husband just had a seizure.

178
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,460
恐怕都不能竞选了
There may not even be an election.

179
00:14:09,460 --> 00:14:10,490
抱歉  我...
I'm sorry. I--

180
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:12,780
如果弗兰西斯挺过来了  我们到时候再处理
If Francis survives, we will deal with this then.

181
00:14:12,780 --> 00:14:15,820
现在  我需要集中关注我眼前的事
Right now, I need to focus on what's right in front of me.

182
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:21,190
没有任何犯罪行为
There was no criminal wrongdoing.

183
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:24,020
这我们理解  但为什么要冒险呢
That we can fathom. But why take the chance?

184
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:26,700
因为保持沉默会让我看上去有罪
Because pleading the Fifth makes it look like I broke the law.

185
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:27,640
我同意
I agree.

186
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:31,700
我会说出真相  我会承认
So I'll tell the truth. I'll own it.

187
00:14:31,890 --> 00:14:34,550
是的  你没有跟他见过面
Yes, that you didn't meet with him.

188
00:14:36,740 --> 00:14:37,670
你是说...
Are you suggesting that--

189
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:40,240
司法部长和希瑟各执一词
It's the Attorney General's word against Heather's.

190
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:43,660
作为你的律师  我不能参与这个对话
As your lawyer, I can't be part of this conversation.

191
00:14:43,660 --> 00:14:45,450
我们还是能赢得竞选的
We can still win this campaign.

192
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:48,670
我去大厅等你
I'll be in the lobby.

193
00:14:58,250 --> 00:14:59,350
我会支持你的说法
I'll back you up.

194
00:14:59,540 --> 00:15:03,030
安保人员只看见我和古德温一起
The security detail only saw me and Goodwin together,

195
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:04,390
没看见你和他
not the two of you.

196
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:10,120
我要宣誓作证的
This is under oath.

197
00:15:10,620 --> 00:15:13,150
安德伍德的人是想抹黑我们
Underwood's people are trying to smear us.

198
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:14,410
这场竞选的全部意义
The whole point of this campaign

199
00:15:14,410 --> 00:15:16,320
就是做与安德伍德截然不同的人
was to be the opposite of Underwood.

200
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,930
我以为你想要这个的
I thought you wanted this.

201
00:15:18,210 --> 00:15:20,100
如果要犯法就不行
Not if it means breaking the law.

202
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:22,580
你觉得换作他  还会有这种犹豫吗
Do you think he'd even be having this conversation?

203
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:26,620
你是真正在意法律的  希瑟
You actually care about the law, Heather...

204
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,790
所以该由你来做总统
which is why you need to be president.

205
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:52,110
-安德伍德夫人  -鲍勃  我不知道...
- Mrs. Underwood. - Bob, I didn't realize--

206
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:55,480
少数党领袖和我正在讨论救市计划
The Leader and I were just discussing the bailout package.

207
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:57,760
布莱斯总统要我强调一下
President Blythe just wanted me to stress

208
00:15:57,760 --> 00:16:01,440
民主党人当前团结一致的重要性
how important it is that the Democrats stick together right now

209
00:16:01,870 --> 00:16:02,910
弗兰西斯还在...
with Francis being--

210
00:16:02,910 --> 00:16:03,320
不必如此
There's no need.

211
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:07,170
我刚给议长打了电话  安排紧急投票
I just called the Speaker to schedule an emergency vote.

212
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:09,400
我相信总统会很满意的
I'm sure the President will be pleased.

213
00:16:09,780 --> 00:16:12,540
-弗兰克怎么样  -他还撑着
- How's Frank? - He's hanging in there.

214
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:15,230
你一定想快点回医院
I'm sure you wanna get back to the hospital.

215
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:17,490
但谢谢你亲自前来
But thank you for making the personal visit.

216
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:19,330
牵挂和祈祷与你同在  克莱尔
Thoughts and prayers, Claire.

217
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:21,000
谢谢你  鲍勃
Thank you, Bob.

218
00:16:21,110 --> 00:16:22,540
我送你出去
I'll walk you out.

219
00:16:23,130 --> 00:16:24,500
失陪一下  领袖
Excuse me, Leader.

220
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,190
你是来威胁我的
You came here to threaten me.

221
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:39,830
我们不必不和的  杰姬
We don't need to be at odds, Jackie.

222
00:16:41,070 --> 00:16:43,110
你打算每次遭遇我的反对
Do you plan on hanging this over my head

223
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:45,050
都拿这个来威胁我吗
every time I try to oppose you?

224
00:16:45,060 --> 00:16:47,470
你自己不小心  可怪不得我
You can't fault me for your sloppiness.

225
00:16:48,170 --> 00:16:49,270
也就是"是"了
That's a "Yes."

226
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:51,330
只要我们是一边的
As long as we're working together,

227
00:16:51,330 --> 00:16:53,410
你就没什么可担心的
you have nothing to worry about.

228
00:16:59,130 --> 00:17:01,500
总统先生  希望您别过于乐观
Mr. President, I wouldn't get your hopes up.

229
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,790
七国集团的成员们
The members of the G7

230
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:05,300
已经因为邀请了俄国而不满了
are already ruffled because Russia was invited,

231
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,510
而佩特罗夫可能会利用这个机会
and Petrov may be using this opportunity 

232
00:17:07,510 --> 00:17:10,310
在国际社会上给我们难堪
to embarrass us in front of the international community.

233
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:10,710
什么事
Yes?

234
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,110
-第一夫人来了  先生  -请她进来
- The First Lady is here, sir. - Send her in.

235
00:17:13,110 --> 00:17:14,920
先生  我想先完成我们的讨论
Sir, I would like to finish our briefing--

236
00:17:14,930 --> 00:17:17,740
第一夫人想见我  我可不能让她等着
I'm not gonna keep the First Lady waiting if she wants to see me.

237
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:22,890
-你听说了吧  -对  博奇几分钟前来电了
- I'm sure you've heard. - Yes, Birch called a few minutes ago.

238
00:17:23,170 --> 00:17:25,760
我想和你一起去勃兰登堡  凯茜
I'd like to join you in Brandenburg, Cathy.

239
00:17:25,910 --> 00:17:28,290
很感谢你愿意出力
Well, I appreciate you wanting to pitch in,

240
00:17:28,290 --> 00:17:30,020
但我真的认为没这必要
but I really don't think that's necessary.

241
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:31,890
我比任何人都了解这个计划
Well, I know this plan better than anyone.

242
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:34,720
-总统先生  -机会只有一次
- Mr. President... - There is only one shot at this.

243
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,350
-所有人都在场  -弗兰克呢
- Everyone at the same table. - What about Frank?

244
00:17:37,860 --> 00:17:40,220
我在勃兰登堡能派上用场  在这里就不能了
In Brandenburg, I can be useful. I can't here.

245
00:17:40,230 --> 00:17:41,240
第一夫人不能
The First Lady cannot

246
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:43,650
代表美国政府进行谈判
negotiate on behalf of the United States government.

247
00:17:43,650 --> 00:17:46,450
谁做代表  由你决定  总统先生
The delegation is at your discretion, Mr. President.

248
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:49,150
有人支持你  或许是好事
It might be good for you to have some support.

249
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:52,210
她的在场会削弱我作为国务卿的权威
Her presence undermines my authority as Secretary of State.

250
00:17:52,210 --> 00:17:56,640
凯茜  佩特罗夫非常固执  这你相信我
Cathy, Petrov is incredibly stubborn. Trust me, I know.

251
00:17:56,810 --> 00:17:59,590
你为什么不愿意用上所有的资源呢
Why wouldn't you wanna have every asset available to you?

252
00:18:00,210 --> 00:18:01,830
请允许我做这件事  总统先生
Allow me to do this, Mr. President.

253
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:03,510
-先生  -如果能增加胜算
- Sir-- - If it increases our chances.

254
00:18:03,510 --> 00:18:05,370
会的  我保证
It will, I promise.

255
00:18:06,950 --> 00:18:09,730
那就一起吧  我们把简报过一遍
Then join us. We're going over the briefing now.

256
00:18:26,210 --> 00:18:27,670
你尽力了  弗兰克
You tried, Frank...

257
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:30,970
这已经比大多数人都强了
which is more than most people ever do.

258
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:33,960
现在  只剩下我们了
Right now, it's just us.

259
00:18:34,670 --> 00:18:36,060
闭上你的眼睛
Rest your eyes.

260
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:39,090
我们有用不完的时间
We have all the time in the world.

261
00:18:46,770 --> 00:18:48,400
丹尼  发生什么事了
Danny, what was that?

262
00:18:51,090 --> 00:18:53,750
-丹尼  -没事  妈妈
- Danny? - Nothing, Mom.

263
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:02,290
把门打开
Open the door.

264
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:06,550
把门打开
Open the door.

265
00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:21,660
安德伍德夫人  萨克逊医生的电话
Mrs. Underwood? Dr. Saxon is on the line.

266
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:25,200
失陪一下
Excuse me.

267
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:32,920
你好
Hello?

268
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:38,000
晚上好  或者说早上好
Good evening, or good morning.

269
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:42,990
安德伍德总统正在准备手术
President Underwood is currently being prepped for surgery

270
00:19:42,990 --> 00:19:45,100
接受肝脏移植
to receive a liver transplant.

271
00:19:46,050 --> 00:19:47,350
不出意外的话
Barring any complications,

272
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:51,000
手术将耗时12到13小时
the surgery is expected to take 12 to 13 hours.

273
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:53,740
有需要的话我们会向大家更新情况
Uh, we'll update you about the progress if need be,

274
00:19:53,740 --> 00:19:57,770
但在手术结束之前应该不会有什么消息了
but probably nothing more until the operation's completed.

275
00:19:57,830 --> 00:20:00,210
我们可以马上让飞机掉头  夫人
We can turn the plane around right now, ma'am.

276
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,530
你能在他手术结束之前赶回去
You'll be back before he's out of surgery.

277
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:06,000
我们应该那样做  克莱尔
We should do that, Claire.

278
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,890
峰会我会迟到  但是大家能
I'll be late to the summit, but everyone will--

279
00:20:07,890 --> 00:20:10,100
不  我们马上就到了
No. We're almost there.

280
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:13,990
-我们继续前进  -说实话  克莱尔
- We keep going. - Honestly, Claire--

281
00:20:13,990 --> 00:20:16,930
-告诉机长保持航线  -是  夫人
- Inform the captain to stay on course. - Yes, ma'am.

282
00:20:20,970 --> 00:20:22,820
请给我接赛斯·格雷森
Connect me with Seth Grayson, please.

283
00:20:28,940 --> 00:20:30,170
他已经进去了
He's already gone in.

284
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:34,630
第一夫人在去勃兰登堡的路上
The First Lady is currently en route to Brandenburg

285
00:20:34,630 --> 00:20:37,680
手术期间不会回到华盛顿
and will not be in Washington for the surgery.

286
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:48,420
她会继续按计划
She will continue onto the G7

287
00:20:48,420 --> 00:20:51,940
在七国峰会中协助杜兰特国务卿
Summit to assist Secretary Durant, as planned.

288
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:55,760
她让我宣读以下声明
She asked me to read the following statement.

289
00:20:57,820 --> 00:21:00,680
"不调头对我来说是个困难的决定"
"It was a difficult decision for me not to return..."

290
00:21:00,730 --> 00:21:04,010
但我了解我的丈夫  如果他醒着
But I know my husband. If he were conscious...

291
00:21:04,010 --> 00:21:05,510
"他会让我继续前行"
"...he'd tell me to press on..."

292
00:21:05,510 --> 00:21:08,490
因为支持他最好的方式就是为国效力
...that the best way to be at his side is to serve my country.

293
00:21:08,490 --> 00:21:11,990
"而我在德国能比在等候室里发挥更大的作用
"And I can serve it better in Germany than in a waiting room.

294
00:21:12,870 --> 00:21:15,420
如果有紧急情况  我会马上回去"
If there's an emergency, I'll return immediately..."

295
00:21:15,420 --> 00:21:16,990
但我对杰弗逊纪念医院的
...but I have the utmost faith...

296
00:21:16,990 --> 00:21:19,570
"医疗团队有极大的信心"
"...in the medical team at Jefferson Memorial."

297
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:21,950
我在祈祷手术成功
I'm praying for a successful procedure,

298
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:26,480
我也请求你们跟我一起为我丈夫
and I ask all of you to join me in praying for my husband,

299
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,120
你们的总统祈祷
your president.

300
00:21:40,380 --> 00:21:41,770
请就坐  邓巴女士
Right over there, Ms. Dunbar.

301
00:21:43,590 --> 00:21:44,630
你的律师会来参加吗
Will your attorneys be joining us?

302
00:21:44,630 --> 00:21:46,830
我已经让我的律师不要来了
I've asked my attorneys not to attend.

303
00:21:47,510 --> 00:21:49,910
我们得说明  为您的利益考虑...
We have to advise you that it's in your best interest--

304
00:21:49,910 --> 00:21:51,830
我很清楚  摩根先生
I'm well aware, Mr. Morgan.

305
00:21:52,510 --> 00:21:54,780
我不是第一次坐上这张桌子了
It's not my first time at this table.

306
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:15,800
谢谢  周主席  佩特罗夫总统
Thank you, President Zhou. President Petrov?

307
00:22:16,260 --> 00:22:18,930
俄罗斯和中国一样希望参与国际峰会
Russia shares China's desire for inclusion.

308
00:22:18,930 --> 00:22:21,690
我们期待展开有成效的会谈
We are looking forward to productive talks.

309
00:22:21,930 --> 00:22:24,420
同时我们也要对安德伍德总统的手术
And we also want to extend our sincere best wishes

310
00:22:24,430 --> 00:22:26,750
致以最真诚的祝福
for President Underwood's surgery.

311
00:22:27,110 --> 00:22:29,040
我们都非常想念他
He is dearly missed at this meeting.

312
00:22:29,900 --> 00:22:31,610
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President.

313
00:22:32,630 --> 00:22:35,000
我们可以开始了吗
So, shall we begin?

314
00:22:38,110 --> 00:22:40,390
当务之急是
The most pressing order of business

315
00:22:40,390 --> 00:22:46,010
联合国际货币基金组织以及美国和中国
is the joint IMF, American-Chinese debt relief package

316
00:22:46,010 --> 00:22:48,240
对俄联邦的债务减免计划
to the Russian Federation.

317
00:22:48,610 --> 00:22:49,620
在录吗
We're recording?

318
00:22:52,620 --> 00:22:54,710
邓巴女士  你所作的任何陈述
Ms. Dunbar, any statement you make

319
00:22:54,710 --> 00:22:57,410
都将记入司法部报告  成为公共记录
will be part of the public record as part of the DOJ report.

320
00:22:57,410 --> 00:22:59,880
虽然这段录像只是为了...
Although this video is simply for purposes of...

321
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:02,120
你可以把录像传给媒体
You can make the video available to the media.

322
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,710
我没有什么好隐瞒的
I have nothing to hide.

323
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,940
你是要放弃对大众保密的权利吗
So you're waiving your right to keep the video from public view?

324
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:08,080
是的
I am.

325
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:10,740
司法部长说你曾向她施压
The attorney general says you pressured her

326
00:23:10,740 --> 00:23:12,110
要她追查卢卡斯·古德温的说法
to look into Lucas Goodwin's claims--

327
00:23:12,110 --> 00:23:14,230
我读过司法部长的陈词
I've read the attorney general's statement.

328
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:16,770
我们还得到一份来自一名年轻女性的证词
We also have a deposition from a young woman,

329
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:18,800
是一名职员  她说古德温
a staffer, who says Goodwin 

330
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:22,490
在3月8日辛辛那提的一场活动中假扮成志愿者
posed as a volunteer at an event in Cincinnati on March 8th.

331
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:25,150
你与古德温先生会过面吗
Did you meet with Mr. Goodwin?

332
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:28,130
我在每场活动上都要与上百人握手
I shake hundreds of people's hands at every event.

333
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:32,360
如果他去过辛辛那提  我有可能跟他握过手
If he was in Cincinnati, there's a chance I may have shaken his.

334
00:23:33,730 --> 00:23:36,780
但要说我跟他曾单独会面...
But the claim that he and I met one-on-one...

335
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,130
所以你是说你没有见过他吗
So you're saying you didn't meet with him?

336
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:43,860
我们有电话记录  邓巴女士
We have phone records, Ms. Dunbar.

337
00:23:43,860 --> 00:23:45,440
你的确曾与司法部长通过话
You did speak to the attorney general.

338
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:48,710
玛莎是我的前任上司和老友
Martha is my former boss and an old friend.

339
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:50,840
我们经常通话  她为什么要说我...
We speak frequently. Why she would claim that I...

340
00:23:50,840 --> 00:23:53,010
我们要个简单的回答  邓巴女士
We need a simple answer, Ms. Dunbar.

341
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:54,920
你是否
Did you or did you not 

342
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:57,630
曾与卢卡斯·古德温在辛辛那提私下见面
meet with Lucas Goodwin privately in Cincinnati?

343
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:06,600
是的
Yes.

344
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:09,620
我与一名不认识的男人见了面
I met with a man I didn't know 

345
00:24:09,620 --> 00:24:11,800
结果发现他精神错乱
who turned out to be unhinged.

346
00:24:12,270 --> 00:24:13,840
我联系司法部长
I contacted the attorney general

347
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:16,550
是因为她是全国顶尖的执法人员
because she's the top law enforcement official in the country

348
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:18,890
而且证人保护计划受她管辖
and WITSEC is under her jurisdiction. 

349
00:24:18,890 --> 00:24:20,420
我没做错什么
I did nothing wrong.

350
00:24:20,430 --> 00:24:21,560
告诉我们这场会面的性质
Tell us the nature of this meeting.

351
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:22,870
我要郑重声明
I'd like to say, for the record,

352
00:24:22,870 --> 00:24:25,900
我认为这次面谈是一场政治阴谋
that I think this interview is an act of political sabotage.

353
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:29,140
其目的就是要通过关联让我看上去有罪
Its goal is to make me look guilty by association,

354
00:24:29,140 --> 00:24:33,260
但表现与事实是两回事
but there are the way things look and the way things actually are.

355
00:24:33,590 --> 00:24:35,640
我调查弗兰克·安德伍德的时候
When I investigated Frank Underwood,

356
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:37,740
他看上去是清白的  但他并不是
he looked innocent, but he wasn't.

357
00:24:37,740 --> 00:24:39,950
我无法证明  可我知道确实如此
I couldn't prove it, but I knew it to be true.

358
00:24:39,950 --> 00:24:40,700
邓巴女士
Ms. Dunbar...

359
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:43,040
你们有我跟古德温先生会面的证据
You have proof that I met with Mr. Goodwin.

360
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:44,380
我已经承认了
I've admitted it.

361
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:47,550
这只能证明我的诚实
All that proves is that I'm honest,

362
00:24:47,670 --> 00:24:50,370
不像总统那样为了个人利益
unlike a president who would use the Department of Justice

363
00:24:50,370 --> 00:24:54,490
利用司法部去攻击他的对手
to target his political opponent for his own personal gain.

364
00:24:54,490 --> 00:24:55,570
我要提醒你  女士
Let me remind you, ma'am, 

365
00:24:55,570 --> 00:24:58,710
总统在这次调查开始前就已陷入昏迷...
the president was unconscious when this investigation began...

366
00:24:58,860 --> 00:25:01,140
不论他是否意识清醒
It doesn't matter whether he was unconscious or not,

367
00:25:01,150 --> 00:25:03,290
不论他是死是活
whether he lives or dies.

368
00:25:03,380 --> 00:25:06,090
为总统效力的人代表的就是他
The president is the people who work for him.

369
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,620
我觉得这事成不了
I don't think this is going to work.

370
00:26:12,620 --> 00:26:14,290
佩特罗夫在会上只是说说而已
Petrov's talking the talk in session,

371
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:16,750
他不肯跟我私下见面
but he won't meet with me privately.

372
00:26:16,850 --> 00:26:19,030
中国人已经准备签字了  如果是因为这个
Chinese are ready to sign, if that's the hold-up.

373
00:26:19,030 --> 00:26:20,430
跟中国人无关
It's not the Chinese.

374
00:26:20,540 --> 00:26:23,920
他拒绝跟任何非国家首脑讲话
He refuses to meet with anyone other than a head of state.

375
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:26,390
那就看看他愿不愿意跟总统夫人见面
Then see if he'll meet with the president's wife.

376
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:31,620
这不能改变他道德败坏的事实
It doesn't change the fact that he is morally corrupt,

377
00:26:28,410 --> 00:26:34,750
{\an8}邓巴曾与古德温见面  承认见面  攻击总统

378
00:26:31,620 --> 00:26:34,800
他也败坏了听命于他的机关
and he has corrupted the institutions that report to him.

379
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,850
所以我才要竞选总统
That is why I am running for president,

380
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:39,630
因为总得有人跟他抗争
because someone needs to fight this.

381
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:41,420
她不止跟古德温见了面
So not only did she meet with Goodwin,

382
00:26:41,420 --> 00:26:44,110
她还利用调查来攻击
she's using the investigation to attack a president

383
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:45,720
这会儿正在手术台上的总统
who's on the operating table as we speak.

384
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,440
是啊  她一直为自己辩护
Yeah, the way she keeps defending herself

385
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:49,070
只会让阴谋论者有更多...
only gives conspiracy theorists more...

386
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:50,120
她完了
She's done.

387
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,640
我不是说她有参与...
Now, I'm not saying that she was involved...

388
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:52,990
毫无疑问
Without a doubt.

389
00:26:52,990 --> 00:26:54,140
...但许多人正在社交媒体上...
...but many are taking to social media...

390
00:26:54,140 --> 00:26:56,280
-赛斯  -你好  辛西娅
- Seth. - Hello, Cynthia.

391
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:57,870
你有没有什么工作给我
